1
00:00:30,322 --> 00:00:33,951
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

2
00:00:44,044 --> 00:00:46,879
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION - SOME
SCENES WERE GENERATED USING AI

3
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:49,048
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

4
00:01:01,770 --> 00:01:03,563
Did you really make it yourself?

5
00:01:05,566 --> 00:01:08,110
All the rice cakes in your fridge
had gone bad, so…

6
00:01:12,364 --> 00:01:15,200
People keep telling me to move on,

7
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:19,621
but you keep giving me reasons
to think about my grandma.

8
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:26,211
It's not like you can control
how you feel.

9
00:01:27,713 --> 00:01:33,760
You can't exactly force yourself
to stop missing someone.

10
00:01:42,185 --> 00:01:43,769
Don't you hate me, Dr. Do?

11
00:01:43,770 --> 00:01:44,938
Mm-mmm.

12
00:01:46,356 --> 00:01:49,651
How could I hate you? I just feel sorry.

13
00:01:53,238 --> 00:01:55,407
I'm sorry I was so mean to you.

14
00:01:58,201 --> 00:02:01,997
I just wanted to pin the blame on you.

15
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:05,208
But looking back…

16
00:02:07,252 --> 00:02:08,879
It's not you I hated.

17
00:02:11,173 --> 00:02:13,759
I think I hated myself.

18
00:02:17,888 --> 00:02:20,432
For the way I made things so hard
for my grandma,

19
00:02:21,683 --> 00:02:23,101
because I couldn't let her go.

20
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:33,069
Wow.

21
00:02:33,070 --> 00:02:36,406
They really are just like
the ones my grandma used to make.

22
00:02:40,827 --> 00:02:41,911
How do you like them?

23
00:02:41,912 --> 00:02:43,872
Hmm…

24
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:49,336
They're really…

25
00:02:50,712 --> 00:02:53,089
- sweet.
- They're sweet?

26
00:02:53,090 --> 00:02:56,467
Sweet? Oh, man. I'm so sorry.

27
00:02:56,468 --> 00:02:58,928
I'll make them better next time.

28
00:02:58,929 --> 00:03:00,971
So they're sweet?

29
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:04,768
I guess you really did learn
from my grandma.

30
00:03:05,936 --> 00:03:07,104
What?

31
00:03:08,647 --> 00:03:11,525
My grandma's red bean
sorghum rice cakes were super sweet.

32
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:14,027
Oh.

33
00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:20,242
Thank you. I really mean it.

34
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:23,619
Hmm…

35
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:26,038
The feeling's mutual.

36
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:27,374
Mmm…

37
00:03:29,793 --> 00:03:30,877
Mmm…

38
00:03:32,003 --> 00:03:33,296
- Ms. Yuk.
- Yeah?

39
00:03:34,256 --> 00:03:35,799
Did you wash your hair?

40
00:03:37,426 --> 00:03:39,219
I'm not sure.

41
00:03:40,637 --> 00:03:42,556
Good enough.

42
00:03:44,433 --> 00:03:46,435
Do I smell like
red bean sorghum rice cakes?

43
00:03:48,186 --> 00:03:49,563
The smell is so strong.

44
00:03:50,981 --> 00:03:52,481
Stop smelling it.

45
00:03:52,482 --> 00:03:55,443
WET PAINT

46
00:03:55,444 --> 00:03:57,403
- They're good.
-  You mean it?

47
00:03:57,404 --> 00:03:58,405
Yeah.

48
00:04:25,766 --> 00:04:28,560
- Good night.
- You too, Ms. Yuk. Go on.

49
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:31,730
Hey, your pants…

50
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:35,942
I got some on mine as well.

51
00:04:38,028 --> 00:04:39,112
Go to bed.

52
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:44,659
Good night.

53
00:04:47,871 --> 00:04:49,414
Oh, man…

54
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:46,763
What's up?

55
00:05:49,432 --> 00:05:50,433
You're still awake?

56
00:05:53,937 --> 00:05:55,105
I can't sleep.

57
00:05:59,359 --> 00:06:03,738
Then do you want to watch a movie…

58
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:09,994
Are you seriously going to enter
a woman's room when she's alone?

59
00:06:09,995 --> 00:06:11,745
I'm so disappointed in you, man.

60
00:06:11,746 --> 00:06:14,708
You shouldn't do that. Nope.

61
00:06:17,711 --> 00:06:19,295
Then… a walk?

62
00:06:19,296 --> 00:06:23,925
Then let's go on a walk together.

63
00:06:24,676 --> 00:06:26,720
Do you want
to watch a movie together?

64
00:06:32,309 --> 00:06:33,560
Yes.

65
00:06:48,283 --> 00:06:49,491
Oh, shit…

66
00:06:51,578 --> 00:06:53,830
What's this?
She left her door open.

67
00:06:56,374 --> 00:06:57,625
Uh, w-why are you awake?

68
00:06:57,626 --> 00:06:59,627
It's only nine o'clock.

69
00:06:59,628 --> 00:07:03,255
Studies have shown that going to bed early
is good for your health, okay?

70
00:07:03,256 --> 00:07:05,842
Dr. Do, you want to grab a beer?

71
00:07:06,718 --> 00:07:07,719
Right now?

72
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:12,348
- You seem busy. Never mind.
- No, what is it? What?

73
00:07:12,349 --> 00:07:14,892
- Okay, then take a seat for a sec.
- Hold on.

74
00:07:14,893 --> 00:07:17,729
You want me to sit?
But I have something to do. Oh, man…

75
00:07:20,774 --> 00:07:23,568
Really? You want to drink beer
so late into the night?

76
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:30,449
If a man you've never seen before
punches in the door code

77
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:34,536
and enters a house where a woman
lives by herself, what could that mean?

78
00:07:34,537 --> 00:07:35,704
What?

79
00:07:37,207 --> 00:07:40,042
I'm just talking about
a close friend of mine.

80
00:07:40,043 --> 00:07:43,087
He said he saw a stranger
enter the door code

81
00:07:43,088 --> 00:07:45,382
and walk right into
his girlfriend's house.

82
00:07:47,217 --> 00:07:51,388
What would you do in that situation?

83
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:55,557
That's a total no-brainer.
I'd ask her who he is.

84
00:07:55,558 --> 00:07:57,727
That's the obvious solution.

85
00:08:00,063 --> 00:08:01,773
A-Ask her?

86
00:08:03,191 --> 00:08:05,693
Well, it may seem like a no-brainer,

87
00:08:05,694 --> 00:08:07,487
but it's actually very complicated.

88
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:10,906
If she's got another guy…

89
00:08:10,907 --> 00:08:13,910
my friend would have to
break up with her, right?

90
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:19,248
But he doesn't think he can do it.

91
00:08:19,249 --> 00:08:22,919
He thinks he likes her
more than he thought.

92
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:27,632
PYEONDONG GODDESS

93
00:08:31,344 --> 00:08:32,679
Pathetic, isn't he?

94
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:38,935
My friend would agree with you.
He said he had no idea he was so pathetic.

95
00:08:42,897 --> 00:08:45,358
When it comes to people
we have feelings for…

96
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:49,320
we all become pathetic.

97
00:08:51,322 --> 00:08:53,616
I suppose you're right.

98
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:58,455
You're the most pathetic guy
I've ever met, after all.

99
00:08:59,664 --> 00:09:04,085
You even gave up your room to Ms. Hari
after she dumped you like that.

100
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:08,088
I wasn't exactly dumped, okay?

101
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:09,715
Then are we done here?

102
00:09:09,716 --> 00:09:11,884
There's actually one more thing--

103
00:09:11,885 --> 00:09:14,720
No, go back inside.
Nothing clears your head like sleep.

104
00:09:14,721 --> 00:09:15,804
- Go.
- I'm not sleepy.

105
00:09:15,805 --> 00:09:17,056
You are. You totally are.

106
00:09:17,057 --> 00:09:20,142
- I haven't even finished my beer.
- No, stop drinking and go to sleep.

107
00:09:20,143 --> 00:09:22,479
- Sleep is the best medicine. Go!
- But it's only nine…

108
00:09:25,732 --> 00:09:27,192
Geez…

109
00:11:15,175 --> 00:11:19,637
EPISODE 9
COURAGE TO FORGIVE

110
00:11:20,346 --> 00:11:21,805
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

111
00:11:21,806 --> 00:11:24,433
I demand to see all the damn doctors!

112
00:11:24,434 --> 00:11:27,311
Doctors, nurses, get out here right now!

113
00:11:27,312 --> 00:11:29,855
Oh, what is it now?
Have you been drinking again?

114
00:11:29,856 --> 00:11:33,400
"What is it now?
Have you been drinking again?"

115
00:11:33,401 --> 00:11:36,446
Do you seriously have no idea
why I'm here?

116
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:40,032
Do you punks
have any idea what you ruined?

117
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:42,785
Do you have any idea what you ruined?

118
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:46,163
So many years of work down the drain.

119
00:11:46,164 --> 00:11:48,207
All for nothing!

120
00:11:48,208 --> 00:11:49,917
Goodness!

121
00:11:51,419 --> 00:11:55,380
Geez, you again?
You really don't let up, do you?

122
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:57,716
Go ahead.
Gimme the spiel again, why don't you?

123
00:11:57,717 --> 00:12:01,887
Medical staff, blah, blah.
Aggravated crime, blah, blah.

124
00:12:01,888 --> 00:12:04,139
Come on, go ahead!

125
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:07,643
It seems I don't need to remind you
of those things, so please stop.

126
00:12:07,644 --> 00:12:12,481
Hey, I guess the governor scolded you
over the incident at the helipad,

127
00:12:12,482 --> 00:12:14,233
but that was because of a patient.

128
00:12:14,234 --> 00:12:16,235
It's not like we did that on purpose.

129
00:12:16,236 --> 00:12:19,280
What did you say? Scolded?

130
00:12:20,365 --> 00:12:22,741
No one's scolding me.
I'm Yeom Byeongcheol!

131
00:12:22,742 --> 00:12:26,370
No one would dare scold me, okay?

132
00:12:26,371 --> 00:12:31,250
They would have never finished building
that helipad without my supervision.

133
00:12:31,251 --> 00:12:33,585
Never would've finished!

134
00:12:33,586 --> 00:12:35,170
You hear me?

135
00:12:35,171 --> 00:12:37,881
You hear me, you bastards?

136
00:12:46,683 --> 00:12:49,226
I think he dislocated his jaw.
Yikes, he definitely did.

137
00:12:49,227 --> 00:12:50,436
You're right.

138
00:12:50,979 --> 00:12:52,854
- You know how to fix it, right?
- No idea.

139
00:12:52,855 --> 00:12:54,773
- Didn't you do this in rotations?
- Me?

140
00:12:54,774 --> 00:12:57,651
I only did it on a mannequin once
when I was a student.

141
00:12:57,652 --> 00:12:59,152
Aren't you a plastic surgeon?

142
00:12:59,153 --> 00:13:01,071
Dislocated jaws are more
a dentistry thing.

143
00:13:01,072 --> 00:13:02,573
- He's drooling.
- Oh, man…

144
00:13:03,491 --> 00:13:06,159
- Lean back against something.
- What do we do?

145
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:14,127
It's going to get worse if we leave it.

146
00:13:14,836 --> 00:13:16,211
Do not move.

147
00:13:18,006 --> 00:13:21,508
Oh, gosh. That's got to hurt.

148
00:13:21,509 --> 00:13:25,221
Yes, we get it. It hurts.

149
00:13:30,435 --> 00:13:32,519
Okay, one, two, three!

150
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:39,527
- Are you okay?
- Damn it.

151
00:13:40,028 --> 00:13:41,194
Oh, come on…

152
00:13:41,195 --> 00:13:42,779
I'll do it.

153
00:13:45,992 --> 00:13:48,326
Please take it easy.

154
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:58,503
Okay, relax. One, two…

155
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:02,007
Oh, man. It won't go back in.

156
00:14:05,553 --> 00:14:10,932
You guys are doing this
on purpose, aren't you?

157
00:14:10,933 --> 00:14:14,019
Just stay still, okay?
You're going to ruin your jaw.

158
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:15,854
Come on, hold still.

159
00:14:15,855 --> 00:14:18,357
- Go easy on me.
- Just let go.

160
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:21,693
I'll do it on the count of three. One…

161
00:14:23,654 --> 00:14:24,989
Got it.

162
00:14:30,995 --> 00:14:34,539
Hey, get over here! You!

163
00:14:34,540 --> 00:14:38,210
You two did that on purpose, didn't you?

164
00:14:38,211 --> 00:14:40,629
Shut it unless
you want it dislocated again.

165
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:41,631
What?

166
00:14:42,507 --> 00:14:47,594
Hey, you prick.
Who are you to tell me to shut my mouth?

167
00:14:51,057 --> 00:14:53,308
Sit.

168
00:14:53,309 --> 00:14:55,353
Hand me the gauze, please. Sit.

169
00:14:56,145 --> 00:14:57,395
Yes, we get it.

170
00:15:02,527 --> 00:15:03,653
One, two…

171
00:15:05,863 --> 00:15:09,449
Don't open your mouth for a while,
or it could become a recurring issue.

172
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:12,120
You…

173
00:15:12,829 --> 00:15:14,622
Make sure to take your meds, okay?

174
00:15:16,124 --> 00:15:19,001
- Why, you--
- Go home. Go on.

175
00:15:22,380 --> 00:15:23,672
Oh, man…

176
00:15:23,673 --> 00:15:25,883
Damn it.

177
00:15:27,510 --> 00:15:29,761
What was he going on about this time?

178
00:15:29,762 --> 00:15:34,100
Word is, the governor took him off
the Pyeondongdo project.

179
00:15:34,851 --> 00:15:37,060
But he's worked him
like a servant for years.

180
00:15:37,061 --> 00:15:39,187
The governor apparently threw a fit

181
00:15:39,188 --> 00:15:41,731
because Byeongcheol ruined
the helipad celebration.

182
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:44,734
Understandable,
since we hijacked his photo op

183
00:15:44,735 --> 00:15:48,238
and stole his thunder.

184
00:15:48,239 --> 00:15:52,326
Gosh, that's so pathetic.
I can't stand pathetic losers like that.

185
00:15:53,703 --> 00:15:59,166
I'm just worried about how much
he's going to take it out on us now.

186
00:15:59,167 --> 00:16:00,918
Hold on.

187
00:16:01,586 --> 00:16:03,588
You've reached the Public Health Center.

188
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:07,632
The grannies are running a fever?

189
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:08,634
How bad is it?

190
00:16:09,552 --> 00:16:11,720
Mmm… I guess there's a cold going around.

191
00:16:11,721 --> 00:16:15,056
Well, since their fevers
aren't too bad right now,

192
00:16:15,057 --> 00:16:17,726
we'll send our staff over tomorrow,
so don't worry.

193
00:16:17,727 --> 00:16:19,478
Yes.

194
00:16:20,438 --> 00:16:22,230
What's going on?

195
00:16:22,231 --> 00:16:25,318
It looks like a cold
is going around Jineondo.

196
00:16:25,902 --> 00:16:27,737
We're going to need you
to head over there.

197
00:16:29,614 --> 00:16:30,697
M-Me?

198
00:16:30,698 --> 00:16:33,867
It's a quick ferry ride. Only one hour.

199
00:16:33,868 --> 00:16:36,036
One hour? That's a long…

200
00:16:36,037 --> 00:16:37,830
I'll go with him.

201
00:16:38,873 --> 00:16:40,582
You're volunteering to go with him?

202
00:16:40,583 --> 00:16:43,461
- Yes.
- With Dr. Do Jiui?

203
00:16:44,086 --> 00:16:45,170
Yes.

204
00:16:45,171 --> 00:16:48,965
I see. I'd be grateful
if you would do that.

205
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:50,634
You can make the first ferry, right?

206
00:16:50,635 --> 00:16:52,135
-  Yes.
-  Okay then.

207
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:53,679
Back to work, everyone.

208
00:16:55,473 --> 00:16:56,933
Thank you for your hard work.

209
00:17:11,906 --> 00:17:14,659
What was that? What is going on?

210
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:19,830
I guess they made up again.

211
00:17:35,054 --> 00:17:36,973
I see you came out early, Dr. Do.

212
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:39,850
Only because you're tagging along.

213
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:43,563
- What's with all the stuff?
- It's nothing.

214
00:17:44,355 --> 00:17:46,023
- Let's go.
- Okay.

215
00:17:53,864 --> 00:17:55,074
After you.

216
00:17:59,954 --> 00:18:03,791
PYEONDONGDO, JINEONDO

217
00:18:14,010 --> 00:18:15,303
Put this on.

218
00:18:16,387 --> 00:18:17,388
Ah…

219
00:18:18,472 --> 00:18:20,516
You put it around your neck like this.

220
00:18:21,642 --> 00:18:22,852
Why did you bring that?

221
00:18:23,728 --> 00:18:26,563
Physical comfort is directly correlated
with peace of mind.

222
00:18:26,564 --> 00:18:28,690
- Want to try it on?
- No, I'm good.

223
00:18:28,691 --> 00:18:31,569
- I'm okay.
- Are you sure? Then…

224
00:18:32,445 --> 00:18:34,989
You want some chocolate
to lighten up your mood?

225
00:18:35,656 --> 00:18:38,908
If not, I have some really
funny comic books too.

226
00:18:38,909 --> 00:18:40,410
BOYHOOD 1
BOYHOOD 2

227
00:18:40,411 --> 00:18:42,538
To take your mind off things.

228
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:46,916
"Boyhood"?

229
00:18:46,917 --> 00:18:48,461
"Lee Myoungwoo"?

230
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:51,546
It's my favorite comic book of all time.

231
00:18:51,547 --> 00:18:53,924
- What else do you have?
- Give me a sec.

232
00:18:54,467 --> 00:18:55,550
Uh…

233
00:18:55,551 --> 00:18:58,387
I've also got a blanket…

234
00:18:59,347 --> 00:19:02,475
and here's some yuja tea I made.

235
00:19:03,684 --> 00:19:06,353
- Try it. To keep you warm.
- I'm good.

236
00:19:06,354 --> 00:19:08,146
- Come on, try it.
- I'll pass.

237
00:19:08,147 --> 00:19:09,148
You don't want it?

238
00:19:14,945 --> 00:19:16,238
This should do the trick.

239
00:19:19,742 --> 00:19:21,369
This is all I need.

240
00:19:22,745 --> 00:19:26,374
I'm going to take a nap.

241
00:19:29,251 --> 00:19:30,877
Sure, go ahead.

242
00:20:01,867 --> 00:20:04,787
Man, just who was he?

243
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:08,957
Maybe I really should just
bite the bullet and ask her.

244
00:20:08,958 --> 00:20:10,418
-  Excuse me!
- Yes?

245
00:20:12,503 --> 00:20:16,340
The public health center's
that way, right?

246
00:20:16,924 --> 00:20:17,925
What?

247
00:20:19,552 --> 00:20:22,930
Yes. You just keep going that way.

248
00:20:25,057 --> 00:20:26,434
Thanks.

249
00:20:35,901 --> 00:20:37,694
What is going on?

250
00:20:37,695 --> 00:20:40,030
Is he on his way to meet Ms. Jeongseon?

251
00:20:44,410 --> 00:20:47,245
He was actually on his way to see me.

252
00:20:47,246 --> 00:20:48,413
What the heck?

253
00:20:48,414 --> 00:20:51,332
So you were the Korean medicine doc?

254
00:20:53,961 --> 00:20:55,212
What brings you in today?

255
00:20:55,921 --> 00:20:59,549
My back's been aching a little.

256
00:21:00,634 --> 00:21:02,970
Uh… Your back?

257
00:21:03,846 --> 00:21:05,138
KIM JIUNG

258
00:21:05,139 --> 00:21:07,266
- Mr. Kim Jiung?
- Yes?

259
00:21:08,184 --> 00:21:10,059
I'll be checking your back now,

260
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:11,854
so tell me if you feel any discomfort.

261
00:21:15,232 --> 00:21:17,108
No issues here. Let's try here.

262
00:21:18,444 --> 00:21:20,278
Mild discomfort.

263
00:21:20,279 --> 00:21:22,655
There!

264
00:21:22,656 --> 00:21:24,574
How long has this been going on?

265
00:21:24,575 --> 00:21:26,409
Well…

266
00:21:26,410 --> 00:21:32,916
I kind of overexerted myself last night.

267
00:21:32,917 --> 00:21:35,585
Ah…

268
00:21:35,586 --> 00:21:38,046
So you pushed yourself
too hard last night, huh?

269
00:21:41,509 --> 00:21:43,426
You've got a lot of muscle knots.

270
00:21:43,427 --> 00:21:44,470
I'll be right back.

271
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:52,644
MY BOO

272
00:21:57,691 --> 00:21:59,609
Babe.

273
00:21:59,610 --> 00:22:03,655
Don't worry about me. I'm totally fine.

274
00:22:03,656 --> 00:22:04,657
Yeah.

275
00:22:06,992 --> 00:22:09,620
I'm good to go again tonight.

276
00:22:10,621 --> 00:22:11,705
Yeah.

277
00:22:15,626 --> 00:22:16,793
It's nothing.

278
00:22:20,214 --> 00:22:21,257
Huh?

279
00:22:22,508 --> 00:22:26,011
So that guy still doesn't know?

280
00:22:26,846 --> 00:22:30,516
Damn, what a ninnyhammer.

281
00:22:31,433 --> 00:22:34,645
Yeah. You're right.

282
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:40,859
And it's not like he would know.

283
00:22:40,860 --> 00:22:43,403
That's what makes him a ninnyhammer,

284
00:22:43,404 --> 00:22:48,741
not that he'd even know
what that means.

285
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:57,585
The back is always a bit sensitive.

286
00:23:01,839 --> 00:23:04,508
I guess you really did
push yourself too hard.

287
00:23:05,509 --> 00:23:07,928
Just wait right here.

288
00:23:08,721 --> 00:23:10,347
Oh, man…

289
00:23:24,445 --> 00:23:27,031
Man, I really am pathetic.

290
00:23:31,452 --> 00:23:33,287
Are you here to see if he's okay?

291
00:23:33,996 --> 00:23:35,915
Have you forgotten that I'm also here?

292
00:23:39,335 --> 00:23:41,629
We need to talk.

293
00:23:43,297 --> 00:23:45,049
Oh, man…

294
00:23:48,427 --> 00:23:49,594
What's this about?

295
00:23:49,595 --> 00:23:51,347
Is there something you want to tell me?

296
00:23:53,349 --> 00:23:54,432
What do you mean?

297
00:23:54,433 --> 00:23:55,851
I saw everything, okay?

298
00:23:56,727 --> 00:24:00,689
What exactly did you see?
You're going to have to elaborate.

299
00:24:02,524 --> 00:24:04,734
I saw that man,
who's lying down in my exam room,

300
00:24:04,735 --> 00:24:07,279
punch in the door code
and enter your house.

301
00:24:07,821 --> 00:24:10,073
Who is that man?

302
00:24:10,074 --> 00:24:14,995
I noticed the way he openly entered
your house like he had nothing to hide.

303
00:24:15,621 --> 00:24:17,623
Dr. Yong, that's…

304
00:24:18,958 --> 00:24:21,042
Well, it's complicated--

305
00:24:21,043 --> 00:24:22,835
What's so complicated about it?

306
00:24:22,836 --> 00:24:26,297
I'll tell you about it
once I've sorted everything out…

307
00:24:26,298 --> 00:24:30,343
- Sorted everything out?
- Just give me some time…

308
00:24:30,344 --> 00:24:31,553
Ms. Eom…

309
00:24:33,555 --> 00:24:34,723
Am I your side piece?

310
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:38,560
Actually, maybe not even a side piece.

311
00:24:39,979 --> 00:24:42,188
- Was I just a casual hookup?
- What?

312
00:24:42,189 --> 00:24:44,691
I'm guessing you're worried
about hurting me,

313
00:24:44,692 --> 00:24:46,610
but just rip the Band-aid off and tell me.

314
00:24:47,695 --> 00:24:51,699
It's not like we were
in a serious relationship or anything.

315
00:24:56,578 --> 00:24:58,247
Oh…

316
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:05,420
If we weren't in a serious relationship,

317
00:25:05,421 --> 00:25:07,840
why do you want to hear
about my personal affairs?

318
00:25:09,425 --> 00:25:11,592
Think whatever you want.

319
00:25:11,593 --> 00:25:13,345
Suit yourself.

320
00:25:53,010 --> 00:25:58,431
Thank you so much for coming all this way.

321
00:25:58,432 --> 00:26:01,142
I'm the village chief of Jineondo.
This way.

322
00:26:01,143 --> 00:26:03,812
Come right this way.

323
00:26:07,316 --> 00:26:08,901
Come quickly.

324
00:26:20,662 --> 00:26:21,996
How are you doing?

325
00:26:21,997 --> 00:26:24,624
Get up. A doctor's here to see you.

326
00:26:24,625 --> 00:26:25,875
Oh, my…

327
00:26:25,876 --> 00:26:27,668
You don't have to get up, ma'am.

328
00:26:27,669 --> 00:26:32,882
Goodness, I'm so sorry
I made you come all this way.

329
00:26:32,883 --> 00:26:34,468
That's quite all right, ma'am.

330
00:26:36,345 --> 00:26:37,470
Goodness…

331
00:26:37,471 --> 00:26:39,514
How long have you had this fever?

332
00:26:39,515 --> 00:26:42,600
It started yesterday afternoon.

333
00:26:42,601 --> 00:26:45,854
I went out for the first time in a while,
so maybe that's why.

334
00:26:46,730 --> 00:26:52,944
I began feeling really cold,
and my body started aching all over.

335
00:26:52,945 --> 00:26:54,655
You're definitely running a fever.

336
00:26:55,572 --> 00:26:57,657
We're going to give you some IV fluids.

337
00:26:57,658 --> 00:26:59,992
We'll add a fever reducer
and an antibiotic to it.

338
00:26:59,993 --> 00:27:03,538
But if the fever doesn't go away,
you'll have to go to a hospital.

339
00:27:03,539 --> 00:27:04,706
Okay.

340
00:27:05,457 --> 00:27:06,458
Start an IV, please.

341
00:27:09,837 --> 00:27:12,339
-  Let's get you set up with an IV.
-  Okay.

342
00:27:12,881 --> 00:27:15,259
Let me pull your sleeve up, okay?

343
00:27:20,722 --> 00:27:23,392
Ma'am, have you been
to the hospital recently?

344
00:27:24,434 --> 00:27:25,601
No.

345
00:27:25,602 --> 00:27:27,646
Oh… Those are IV marks.

346
00:27:29,147 --> 00:27:30,440
Ah…

347
00:27:31,316 --> 00:27:37,823
These are from a nutritional supplement IV
I got on the mainland a few days ago.

348
00:27:38,824 --> 00:27:43,954
Goodness, I don't know
where my head is at.

349
00:27:50,085 --> 00:27:52,588
- This is going to sting a little.
-  Ah…

350
00:27:55,340 --> 00:27:59,052
Relax. There.

351
00:28:00,679 --> 00:28:02,179
Relax.

352
00:28:54,983 --> 00:28:56,735
I think her fever's gone down a bit.

353
00:28:59,863 --> 00:29:02,114
It looks like she's fallen asleep.

354
00:29:02,115 --> 00:29:03,992
Do you want to step outside for a bit?

355
00:29:06,078 --> 00:29:07,495
Quietly…

356
00:29:07,496 --> 00:29:08,997
Leave it.

357
00:29:14,211 --> 00:29:17,296
Gosh, it's freezing.
The wind is picking up quite a bit.

358
00:29:18,423 --> 00:29:20,425
I wonder if they'll suspend
ferry operations.

359
00:29:21,134 --> 00:29:23,261
What are you thinking about right now?

360
00:29:23,887 --> 00:29:26,722
No, it's not like that, okay?

361
00:29:26,723 --> 00:29:28,557
What did you want to do if they did?

362
00:29:28,558 --> 00:29:30,643
I was just worried about you, okay?

363
00:29:30,644 --> 00:29:34,731
If the high winds were
to rock the boat or something, then…

364
00:29:35,607 --> 00:29:37,109
So you were worried about me?

365
00:29:40,195 --> 00:29:44,532
By the way,
why haven't you asked me about it yet?

366
00:29:44,533 --> 00:29:45,701
Hmm?

367
00:29:46,410 --> 00:29:48,954
About why I get so terrified
out on the water.

368
00:29:51,289 --> 00:29:52,374
Ah…

369
00:29:53,917 --> 00:29:58,088
I just didn't want to
make things harder for you.

370
00:30:00,841 --> 00:30:02,467
Later…

371
00:30:03,969 --> 00:30:06,596
Tell me later when you're ready to share.

372
00:30:11,268 --> 00:30:13,061
Doctor!

373
00:30:14,187 --> 00:30:15,188
Doctor!

374
00:30:15,814 --> 00:30:16,815
Doctor.

375
00:30:18,567 --> 00:30:19,942
What do we do?

376
00:30:19,943 --> 00:30:21,652
Did something happen to the patient?

377
00:30:21,653 --> 00:30:23,070
That's not it.

378
00:30:23,071 --> 00:30:26,574
Ferry service has been suspended today
due to the strong winds.

379
00:30:31,038 --> 00:30:32,830
Uh… Really?

380
00:30:32,831 --> 00:30:35,416
I'm sorry to inconvenience you like this.

381
00:30:35,417 --> 00:30:36,917
Not at all, sir. I'm glad.

382
00:30:36,918 --> 00:30:38,045
Huh?

383
00:30:39,421 --> 00:30:42,548
I'm glad for the opportunity
to examine the patients more closely.

384
00:30:42,549 --> 00:30:45,718
- That's why I'm glad.
- Yes, examine the patients…

385
00:30:45,719 --> 00:30:48,888
Wow, thank you so much.

386
00:30:48,889 --> 00:30:52,016
- Let me know if there's anything you need.
- Okay.

387
00:30:52,017 --> 00:30:53,560
I'll be going now.

388
00:31:02,110 --> 00:31:04,361
-  Welcome.
- Hello.

389
00:31:04,362 --> 00:31:05,529
What's this?

390
00:31:05,530 --> 00:31:08,074
Well, if it isn't the Korean medicine doc.

391
00:31:08,075 --> 00:31:10,493
I guess you're here
to get some groceries, huh?

392
00:31:10,494 --> 00:31:12,453
Ice cream?

393
00:31:12,454 --> 00:31:13,621
Conefare?

394
00:31:13,622 --> 00:31:15,707
Let's just pay up and leave.

395
00:31:17,167 --> 00:31:18,918
What the heck are you doing?

396
00:31:18,919 --> 00:31:20,504
I said let's pay up and leave.

397
00:31:21,088 --> 00:31:22,213
Let go.

398
00:31:22,214 --> 00:31:23,297
Come on.

399
00:31:23,298 --> 00:31:24,632
I said let go!

400
00:31:24,633 --> 00:31:26,551
You're creeping me out!

401
00:31:29,513 --> 00:31:30,596
Oh, doc.

402
00:31:30,597 --> 00:31:33,100
I'm going to drop in tomorrow
as well.

403
00:31:33,850 --> 00:31:36,685
Hot damn, you really are a great doctor.

404
00:31:36,686 --> 00:31:38,521
Ever since I got that treatment,

405
00:31:38,522 --> 00:31:41,273
I've had no issues gyrating my hips
like this, you know?

406
00:31:41,274 --> 00:31:42,483
You get what I mean?

407
00:31:42,484 --> 00:31:45,569
Stop bothering the man
and let's just go, okay?

408
00:31:46,988 --> 00:31:49,324
Just give me a damn second.

409
00:31:50,075 --> 00:31:51,952
Or you're gonna get it!

410
00:31:53,161 --> 00:31:54,204
Stop it.

411
00:31:55,664 --> 00:31:57,666
What the heck?

412
00:31:58,250 --> 00:31:59,959
Stop treating her like a doormat.

413
00:32:03,213 --> 00:32:06,466
Hey, doc. What gives?

414
00:32:09,803 --> 00:32:10,804
Oh…

415
00:32:12,848 --> 00:32:14,307
Try smiling for me.

416
00:32:14,808 --> 00:32:16,351
Are you nuts?

417
00:32:19,396 --> 00:32:21,398
Just smile for me, okay?

418
00:32:22,816 --> 00:32:24,234
You heard the doctor. Smile!

419
00:32:25,318 --> 00:32:26,653
What the heck?

420
00:32:27,571 --> 00:32:28,905
What's wrong with my face?

421
00:32:46,506 --> 00:32:48,674
Don't worry too much.

422
00:32:48,675 --> 00:32:49,926
You'll be fine.

423
00:32:54,931 --> 00:32:56,349
It's facial nerve palsy.

424
00:32:57,434 --> 00:32:59,602
I'll prescribe danggui buxue decoction

425
00:32:59,603 --> 00:33:02,022
to enrich his blood
and replenish his energy.

426
00:33:02,772 --> 00:33:06,526
Tomorrow, you can take the first ferry
back to the mainland to get it treated.

427
00:33:08,653 --> 00:33:09,654
Okay.

428
00:33:36,473 --> 00:33:40,392
Why take care of the boyfriend of the girl
you're just hooking up with?

429
00:33:40,393 --> 00:33:42,145
You could have just ignored him.

430
00:33:47,400 --> 00:33:49,736
Why are you being so nice to him?

431
00:33:54,616 --> 00:33:56,617
Because seeing that man in pain…

432
00:34:00,538 --> 00:34:02,290
…would have made you sad.

433
00:34:04,751 --> 00:34:06,586
I didn't want to see you sad.

434
00:34:15,345 --> 00:34:16,680
Hey.

435
00:34:19,557 --> 00:34:21,017
Hey!

436
00:34:31,611 --> 00:34:33,780
She deserves someone who treats her well.

437
00:34:34,406 --> 00:34:35,407
What?

438
00:34:36,992 --> 00:34:38,826
What is it?

439
00:34:38,827 --> 00:34:40,369
Mom's calling.

440
00:34:40,370 --> 00:34:42,538
Hurry up and take it, doofus.

441
00:34:42,539 --> 00:34:43,622
"Doofus"?

442
00:34:43,623 --> 00:34:44,873
Now you're asking for it…

443
00:34:44,874 --> 00:34:48,335
Come on, she was asking me
to put you on the phone, sis.

444
00:34:48,336 --> 00:34:49,878
She hung up.

445
00:34:49,879 --> 00:34:50,964
"Sis"?

446
00:34:52,257 --> 00:34:55,843
You'd better not go
blabbering to Mom again, okay?

447
00:34:55,844 --> 00:34:57,720
- Don't make her worry.
-  Are you insane?

448
00:34:57,721 --> 00:35:00,180
Of course I'm not going
to tell Mom anything.

449
00:35:07,731 --> 00:35:11,818
Are you two siblings?

450
00:35:13,486 --> 00:35:15,196
What are you talking about?

451
00:35:17,157 --> 00:35:19,117
What the heck did you think we were?

452
00:35:22,329 --> 00:35:23,330
No way.

453
00:35:24,247 --> 00:35:25,248
Her and me?

454
00:35:26,041 --> 00:35:28,126
Geez, doc.

455
00:35:28,627 --> 00:35:30,919
How could you be so blind?

456
00:35:30,920 --> 00:35:33,088
Me? With someone like her?

457
00:35:33,089 --> 00:35:34,798
Gosh…

458
00:35:34,799 --> 00:35:37,760
But when I checked your chart,
you had a different last name.

459
00:35:37,761 --> 00:35:41,348
Your name's Kim Jiung,
but her name is Eom Jeongseon.

460
00:35:42,182 --> 00:35:43,683
We have different fathers!

461
00:35:47,604 --> 00:35:50,690
I told you I'd tell you
once I've sorted everything out, didn't I?

462
00:35:51,274 --> 00:35:54,693
I'll bet Your Highness would have
never imagined something like this.

463
00:35:54,694 --> 00:35:59,615
I was looking for a way to tell you
without embarrassing myself, damn it!

464
00:35:59,616 --> 00:36:01,993
Oh, man. What's going on…

465
00:36:03,745 --> 00:36:04,829
Ms. Eom!

466
00:36:07,082 --> 00:36:10,250
Ms. Eom. I'm sorry. I just--

467
00:36:10,251 --> 00:36:11,669
Don't try to stop me.

468
00:36:11,670 --> 00:36:13,837
I'm way more humiliated
than you are right now.

469
00:36:13,838 --> 00:36:17,007
Tell him to come straight home
once he's done with the treatment.

470
00:36:17,008 --> 00:36:18,259
He needs to pack.

471
00:36:33,358 --> 00:36:35,025
Oh…

472
00:36:35,026 --> 00:36:38,697
I already got permission from the owner,
so you can use this room.

473
00:36:40,115 --> 00:36:42,950
But I guess only one room was available.

474
00:36:42,951 --> 00:36:46,203
That's understandable. Finding a room
at the last moment can't be easy.

475
00:36:46,204 --> 00:36:48,289
We're just grateful we got a room at all.

476
00:36:49,082 --> 00:36:51,083
It's not the only one.

477
00:36:51,084 --> 00:36:53,711
You can use this room, miss.

478
00:36:53,712 --> 00:36:57,048
As for you, Doctor,
you can use the room over there.

479
00:37:01,094 --> 00:37:03,011
Oh, that one.

480
00:37:03,012 --> 00:37:05,806
What were you expecting?
Were you going to use one room?

481
00:37:05,807 --> 00:37:08,225
Oh, not at all.

482
00:37:08,226 --> 00:37:10,018
Me? Not at all, sir.

483
00:37:10,019 --> 00:37:13,605
Goodness, how could you even
consider staying in the same room?

484
00:37:13,606 --> 00:37:15,357
That's so inappropriate.

485
00:37:15,358 --> 00:37:18,152
People think if you get stranded
when the ferry stops running,

486
00:37:18,153 --> 00:37:19,737
there's only one room available.

487
00:37:19,738 --> 00:37:21,822
But that's a thing of the past.

488
00:37:21,823 --> 00:37:26,368
Nowadays,
we've got plenty of rooms to spare

489
00:37:26,369 --> 00:37:28,204
since everyone's left for the mainland.

490
00:37:29,247 --> 00:37:31,874
Oh, I see.

491
00:37:31,875 --> 00:37:34,043
Now then, rest well.

492
00:37:41,050 --> 00:37:43,135
You should go in and rest now.

493
00:37:43,136 --> 00:37:44,220
You must be exhausted.

494
00:37:45,680 --> 00:37:48,349
I'll go to that room over there.

495
00:37:48,933 --> 00:37:50,310
The one over there.

496
00:37:51,895 --> 00:37:52,896
Right.

497
00:37:53,480 --> 00:37:54,481
Hmm.

498
00:38:08,203 --> 00:38:09,954
You're such a gentleman.

499
00:38:13,708 --> 00:38:14,792
Huh?

500
00:38:14,793 --> 00:38:19,631
You're seriously going to that room?
Because there are two?

501
00:38:21,174 --> 00:38:22,257
Huh?

502
00:38:22,258 --> 00:38:24,802
You're a real stickler for traffic laws,
aren't you?

503
00:38:24,803 --> 00:38:28,431
I bet you obey traffic signals to a T
and never cross the stop line.

504
00:38:32,519 --> 00:38:33,936
Oh, that's right.

505
00:38:33,937 --> 00:38:36,856
You're a nice boy who doesn't like
crossing the line, aren't you?

506
00:38:38,775 --> 00:38:40,193
Good night.

507
00:38:45,949 --> 00:38:46,950
No, I'm not.

508
00:38:50,495 --> 00:38:51,579
Just a sec.

509
00:39:05,468 --> 00:39:06,469
I'm…

510
00:39:09,013 --> 00:39:10,181
not nice.

511
00:39:42,297 --> 00:39:43,381
What the…

512
00:39:51,222 --> 00:39:52,556
Sir…

513
00:39:52,557 --> 00:39:54,808
- This is really bad!
-  Huh?

514
00:39:54,809 --> 00:39:57,978
The grannies are all burning up!

515
00:39:57,979 --> 00:40:01,732
Hurry up and come with me, hurry!

516
00:40:19,250 --> 00:40:22,002
Ma'am, can you hear me?

517
00:40:22,003 --> 00:40:24,129
Why is this happening to them all at once?

518
00:40:24,130 --> 00:40:26,131
Is there some kind of plague going around?

519
00:40:28,676 --> 00:40:30,302
- Start an IV, please.
- Okay.

520
00:40:30,303 --> 00:40:31,637
Goodness.

521
00:40:31,638 --> 00:40:35,058
I'm worried they might all
end up passing away at this rate.

522
00:40:47,695 --> 00:40:50,114
Dr. Do, here…

523
00:41:02,752 --> 00:41:07,464
Ma'am, did you also get
a nutritional supplement IV?

524
00:41:07,465 --> 00:41:09,299
Why do you ask?

525
00:41:09,300 --> 00:41:11,093
I need to know where they got them.

526
00:41:11,094 --> 00:41:13,096
- Well…
- Hurry!

527
00:41:14,055 --> 00:41:15,138
Well…

528
00:41:15,139 --> 00:41:19,978
I did drop by Ms. Hwang's place, but…

529
00:41:21,312 --> 00:41:23,064
Who is this Ms. Hwang?

530
00:41:25,650 --> 00:41:27,110
Well…

531
00:41:32,031 --> 00:41:33,157
This way…

532
00:41:51,968 --> 00:41:54,554
What brings you here?

533
00:41:56,055 --> 00:41:58,266
What did you give those patients?

534
00:41:59,017 --> 00:42:00,100
Sorry?

535
00:42:00,101 --> 00:42:02,895
I'm asking you what exactly
was in those IVs!

536
00:42:10,820 --> 00:42:12,321
SD 1-4

537
00:42:13,322 --> 00:42:14,824
5%DW
DEXTROSE INJ. 5%

538
00:42:16,701 --> 00:42:18,953
EXPIRATION DATE
NOVEMBER 9, 2024

539
00:42:20,997 --> 00:42:23,499
I try to take good care of them,

540
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:27,670
but the sudden cold snap
must've frozen them a bit.

541
00:42:28,671 --> 00:42:30,839
But that's only a problem in the summer.

542
00:42:30,840 --> 00:42:33,633
A little winter freeze
doesn't do any harm.

543
00:42:33,634 --> 00:42:36,512
Do you know how dangerous it is
to illegally administer IV fluids?

544
00:42:38,431 --> 00:42:39,766
It's not completely illegal.

545
00:42:40,850 --> 00:42:44,937
Ms. Hwang here used to be a nurse,
so she's no different from a doctor.

546
00:42:48,107 --> 00:42:49,442
I'm sorry.

547
00:42:50,401 --> 00:42:52,445
I wanted to come clean from the start,

548
00:42:53,488 --> 00:42:55,573
but I couldn't work up
the courage to do so.

549
00:43:01,120 --> 00:43:04,207
Are the grannies in bad shape?

550
00:43:05,291 --> 00:43:06,292
Yes.

551
00:43:09,378 --> 00:43:12,380
Let's let our center know
that we'll need more antibiotics.

552
00:43:12,381 --> 00:43:14,842
- Let the local center know too.
- Okay.

553
00:43:17,136 --> 00:43:18,929
What'll happen if you let them know?

554
00:43:18,930 --> 00:43:22,099
Won't they take Ms. Hwang away in cuffs?

555
00:43:22,100 --> 00:43:23,892
We'll have to conduct an investigation.

556
00:43:23,893 --> 00:43:24,976
Please don't!

557
00:43:24,977 --> 00:43:27,229
How will we get by
if Ms. Hwang gets taken away?

558
00:43:27,230 --> 00:43:30,273
Administering IV without
a doctor's prescription is illegal, sir!

559
00:43:30,274 --> 00:43:33,193
Damn it,
I told you Ms. Hwang's also a nurse!

560
00:43:33,194 --> 00:43:35,821
We're all alone on this island
without doctors or nurses,

561
00:43:35,822 --> 00:43:41,035
so you'd be signing our death warrants
if you took Ms. Hwang away from us!

562
00:43:42,411 --> 00:43:46,957
On an island like this,
even the common cold can claim lives.

563
00:43:46,958 --> 00:43:50,878
Even the common cold can claim many lives.

564
00:43:51,546 --> 00:43:55,049
Getting sick on an island means death!

565
00:43:57,718 --> 00:44:01,055
Illegal or not, that's none of our concern

566
00:44:01,806 --> 00:44:05,309
because we won't survive long
without Ms. Hwang here anyway!

567
00:44:07,103 --> 00:44:11,357
Do you have any idea how it felt

568
00:44:12,775 --> 00:44:15,278
for me to lose my only child
to a mere cold?

569
00:44:16,904 --> 00:44:20,491
It's an insult to our humanity, okay?

570
00:44:21,617 --> 00:44:24,620
We feel completely abandoned.

571
00:44:25,454 --> 00:44:29,542
So promise me you won't report her, okay?

572
00:44:30,376 --> 00:44:35,464
Please promise me
that you won't report her!

573
00:44:37,383 --> 00:44:38,800
Dr. Hyeon,

574
00:44:38,801 --> 00:44:41,554
it appears some contaminated
IV fluids were administered in Jineondo,

575
00:44:42,138 --> 00:44:43,680
and we're in need of antibiotics.

576
00:44:43,681 --> 00:44:45,474
Can you come here right away?

577
00:44:52,148 --> 00:44:55,026
Isn't it an emergency
if contaminated IV fluid was administered?

578
00:44:57,570 --> 00:44:59,905
Let's just keep an eye
on the situation for now.

579
00:44:59,906 --> 00:45:01,907
What about the local center and police?

580
00:45:01,908 --> 00:45:04,117
The residents don't want
to cause any trouble.

581
00:45:04,118 --> 00:45:06,870
They also want to be treated here
since going to the mainland

582
00:45:06,871 --> 00:45:08,371
could get them in trouble.

583
00:45:08,372 --> 00:45:10,458
What kind of nonsense is…

584
00:45:11,209 --> 00:45:12,959
We have to report this right now.

585
00:45:12,960 --> 00:45:17,131
Those IV fluids are the only thing
the villagers here can rely on

586
00:45:18,299 --> 00:45:20,885
because they don't have
a public health center.

587
00:45:24,931 --> 00:45:27,016
They also agreed
to stop administering them.

588
00:45:28,976 --> 00:45:31,145
Then we'll end up taking the fall for it.

589
00:45:32,688 --> 00:45:35,441
And not a single person
will step up to protect us.

590
00:45:39,403 --> 00:45:40,988
- Dr. Hyeon.
- How strange.

591
00:45:41,781 --> 00:45:45,117
You normally play it by the book,
but you're making an exception here.

592
00:45:46,035 --> 00:45:48,870
This is clearly
an illegal medical practice.

593
00:45:48,871 --> 00:45:51,123
If you won't report her, I will.

594
00:46:01,759 --> 00:46:02,927
Dr. Do.

595
00:46:05,263 --> 00:46:06,430
Oh…

596
00:46:30,830 --> 00:46:32,623
Why is it so cold?

597
00:46:36,460 --> 00:46:38,044
You'll get better in no time.

598
00:46:38,045 --> 00:46:41,716
Goodness, thank you.

599
00:46:44,927 --> 00:46:48,431
JINEONDO VILLAGE HALL

600
00:47:07,158 --> 00:47:09,243
You reported her?

601
00:47:10,661 --> 00:47:13,705
Despite everything I told you!

602
00:47:13,706 --> 00:47:19,795
It's not like you'll come to us
every time someone gets sick!

603
00:47:20,880 --> 00:47:24,966
Are you going to be here every other day,

604
00:47:24,967 --> 00:47:28,220
every time we're staring death in the eye?

605
00:47:29,013 --> 00:47:31,973
It's not like
you ever did anything for us!

606
00:47:31,974 --> 00:47:35,727
What were you doing
as my son lay dying?

607
00:47:35,728 --> 00:47:41,359
What were you doing?

608
00:47:44,862 --> 00:47:47,114
Seonu!

609
00:47:47,823 --> 00:47:50,242
Seonu!

610
00:47:54,372 --> 00:47:57,458
Seonu!

611
00:47:59,251 --> 00:48:01,420
What were you doing?

612
00:48:02,505 --> 00:48:04,839
What have you ever done?

613
00:48:04,840 --> 00:48:07,133
What did any of you do for us?

614
00:48:07,134 --> 00:48:09,887
What did you do for us?

615
00:48:14,308 --> 00:48:15,309
Stop it, sir.

616
00:48:16,352 --> 00:48:17,937
I was the one who reported her.

617
00:48:18,729 --> 00:48:20,897
It was the best thing for the residents.

618
00:48:50,553 --> 00:48:52,721
Did you have to do it?

619
00:48:55,266 --> 00:48:57,852
We could have looked for
a different solution.

620
00:49:00,521 --> 00:49:01,689
What other solution?

621
00:49:03,232 --> 00:49:05,567
You mean letting anyone
stick needles into people

622
00:49:05,568 --> 00:49:07,820
because they have no access to a doctor?

623
00:49:12,241 --> 00:49:15,911
Sure, doing as the residents say
might make things easier for us now,

624
00:49:16,495 --> 00:49:19,540
but when something really bad happens,
the blame will fall on us.

625
00:49:21,667 --> 00:49:24,586
And when that happens,
we won't be able to protect them,

626
00:49:24,587 --> 00:49:26,130
or ourselves.

627
00:49:27,631 --> 00:49:31,135
Why are you taking this
so personally, Dr. Do?

628
00:49:36,223 --> 00:49:38,434
It's because I know how scary it can be…

629
00:49:41,812 --> 00:49:44,148
to have no one around to help
when you need it.

630
00:50:21,810 --> 00:50:24,521
If you have something to say,
just say it.

631
00:50:24,522 --> 00:50:26,815
Instead of following me around like that.

632
00:50:28,359 --> 00:50:29,360
I'm sorry.

633
00:50:38,327 --> 00:50:40,662
Did I or did I not ask you
to give me some time?

634
00:50:40,663 --> 00:50:42,789
How could you do that to me?

635
00:50:42,790 --> 00:50:45,792
What kind of person do you take me for,
that you couldn't even wait

636
00:50:45,793 --> 00:50:48,253
before you decided to jump
to such a gross conclusion?

637
00:50:48,254 --> 00:50:51,131
Why couldn't you trust me?

638
00:50:56,887 --> 00:51:00,015
It wasn't because I couldn't trust you.

639
00:51:00,849 --> 00:51:02,560
It's because I was afraid.

640
00:51:04,019 --> 00:51:07,356
I was afraid you might like someone else
more than you like me.

641
00:51:10,651 --> 00:51:12,695
I was so pathetic.

642
00:51:16,574 --> 00:51:18,325
I'm so scared, you see.

643
00:51:20,995 --> 00:51:23,289
I like you so much…

644
00:51:24,498 --> 00:51:27,459
and I'm scared you're going to
like someone else more than me.

645
00:51:29,211 --> 00:51:30,379
But you see…

646
00:51:33,007 --> 00:51:35,342
I know this is going to
sound really pathetic,

647
00:51:36,802 --> 00:51:39,513
but let me make
just one more pathetic request.

648
00:51:40,889 --> 00:51:42,308
Please forgive me.

649
00:51:45,102 --> 00:51:47,521
I can't break up with you, Ms. Eom.

650
00:51:49,273 --> 00:51:50,274
Okay?

651
00:51:51,650 --> 00:51:53,819
Just give me one last chance.

652
00:52:02,369 --> 00:52:04,788
I'm way more pathetic than you.

653
00:52:07,750 --> 00:52:10,335
I also kept it from you
because I was scared.

654
00:52:10,336 --> 00:52:14,256
I don't know why I get so embarrassed
about everything when I'm around you.

655
00:52:15,466 --> 00:52:17,968
I was worried
that you might judge me for it.

656
00:52:19,136 --> 00:52:20,721
Don't say that.

657
00:52:22,389 --> 00:52:24,390
Because it's all my fault.

658
00:52:24,391 --> 00:52:28,354
It's all my fault.

659
00:52:30,564 --> 00:52:32,106
Oh, yeah.

660
00:52:32,107 --> 00:52:33,776
Jiung left.

661
00:52:35,694 --> 00:52:36,695
What?

662
00:52:37,529 --> 00:52:40,699
I'm saying I'm all alone at home now.

663
00:52:41,408 --> 00:52:42,743
Uh…

664
00:52:45,621 --> 00:52:49,583
Does that mean you forgive me?

665
00:52:51,043 --> 00:52:52,836
Do I have to spell it out for you?

666
00:52:58,133 --> 00:52:59,385
You mean it?

667
00:53:02,096 --> 00:53:04,014
Oh, and that.

668
00:53:12,815 --> 00:53:14,817
What's this?

669
00:53:16,652 --> 00:53:18,736
Can't you tell?

670
00:53:18,737 --> 00:53:20,823
I stitched it up for you.

671
00:53:24,451 --> 00:53:25,869
Ms. Eom.

672
00:53:27,121 --> 00:53:30,124
Just how long were you going to
wear a shirt with a hole in it?

673
00:53:32,251 --> 00:53:33,418
And no more crying!

674
00:53:36,547 --> 00:53:37,798
Thank you.

675
00:53:45,305 --> 00:53:46,890
I love you, Ms. Eom.

676
00:54:06,952 --> 00:54:11,164
He looked downcast all day,
so I told him he could clock out early.

677
00:54:11,165 --> 00:54:13,584
Oh, I see.

678
00:54:14,084 --> 00:54:18,921
By the way, why is Dr. Jiui
so obsessed with Jineondo anyway?

679
00:54:18,922 --> 00:54:22,384
It's not like we could let them
keep operating an illegal pharmacy.

680
00:54:22,968 --> 00:54:26,804
Gosh, just when you think
you know someone.

681
00:54:26,805 --> 00:54:28,598
I mean, normally,

682
00:54:28,599 --> 00:54:31,685
he's such a stickler for the rules
who plays it by the book.

683
00:54:33,771 --> 00:54:34,980
I just don't get him.

684
00:54:35,481 --> 00:54:39,484
I don't get him at all.

685
00:55:55,018 --> 00:55:57,854
Captain, he's going to die!
Please go faster!

686
00:55:58,855 --> 00:56:03,109
Seonu!

687
00:56:03,110 --> 00:56:04,194
Seonu.

688
00:56:06,321 --> 00:56:08,239
I'm not getting a pulse.

689
00:56:11,326 --> 00:56:12,327
Seonu!

690
00:56:13,078 --> 00:56:14,329
Seonu!

691
00:56:45,235 --> 00:56:46,278
Oh, Ms. Yuk.

692
00:56:57,748 --> 00:57:02,085
Winter sure seems to arrive early
on an island.

693
00:57:08,550 --> 00:57:11,386
You don't have to put on
a brave face for me.

694
00:57:16,725 --> 00:57:19,311
I know you're struggling a lot.

695
00:57:24,358 --> 00:57:26,902
You were always by my side.

696
00:57:29,071 --> 00:57:32,157
So I also want to be by your side.

697
00:57:33,909 --> 00:57:38,330
But I'm afraid that if I'm not careful,
I'll end up hurting you.

698
00:57:45,170 --> 00:57:47,172
Can you tell me about what happened?

699
00:57:51,760 --> 00:57:53,804
So you don't have to harbor it alone.

700
00:58:00,602 --> 00:58:02,688
I don't think
we deserve to be happy.

701
00:58:08,402 --> 00:58:10,404
That wouldn't be fair to Seonu.

702
00:59:00,495 --> 00:59:02,205
I don't think I can do it.

703
00:59:18,805 --> 00:59:20,974
I don't think I can
keep doing this either.

704
00:59:23,685 --> 00:59:27,062
I'm done sitting on the sidelines
while you suffer.

705
00:59:27,063 --> 00:59:28,940
I'm not going to leave you alone.

706
00:59:30,817 --> 00:59:32,611
Because that's what you did for me.

707
00:59:37,115 --> 00:59:38,575
So please…

708
00:59:45,665 --> 00:59:47,751
lean on me.

709
01:01:21,011 --> 01:01:23,888
IT'S NOT YOU I HATED…

710
01:01:23,889 --> 01:01:30,645
I THINK I HATED MYSELF

711
01:01:39,821 --> 01:01:43,074
COME ON, TAKE A DIP WITH ME

712
01:01:51,917 --> 01:01:53,417
FILMING OUT ON THE WATER MEANS

713
01:01:53,418 --> 01:01:55,086
THERE'S NOWHERE TO HIDE
FROM THE SUN

714
01:01:59,174 --> 01:02:02,093
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

715
01:02:02,761 --> 01:02:04,846
A PH doc on medication?

716
01:02:05,722 --> 01:02:08,974
I was kind of hoping
to get examined by a different doctor.

717
01:02:08,975 --> 01:02:10,601
Dr. Do Jiui!

718
01:02:10,602 --> 01:02:13,229
I can't take this anymore.

719
01:02:13,772 --> 01:02:15,606
I'm here to meet Jiui.

720
01:02:15,607 --> 01:02:16,983
Dr. Do Jiui?

721
01:02:18,735 --> 01:02:21,029
I know Jiui
better than anyone else.

722
01:02:21,613 --> 01:02:23,782
That's what I wanted
to hear from you most.

723
01:02:25,659 --> 01:02:28,453
Please convince him to leave this island.

724
01:02:31,665 --> 01:02:33,667
Translated by Yoon Hyuk Park
